race.comment: PAW QUANDA (2) turned spotting a big start finishing sixth (23.97) last time in a Grade 4/5 at this track. Solid record at the distance winning four races. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to her credit. Ready to return to form. PAW TEMPE (1) was a last start winner (23.51) from Box 8 at Mt Gambier. Has a solid record from this box including two wins and a minor placing. Shapes as a top winning chance on latest effort. SEATS TWO (3) was prominent early from the tricky draw and did a fair job to be beaten 5 lengths into third (23.41) at Mt Gambier in a Grade 5 over 400m. Form from her last run is proving strong. Hard to beat again. TINKER DOT (7) placed last time at big odds - worth some thought.
